	<TextInfo>
		<Text Type="Business Summary" lastModified="2015-03-07T02:24:34">International Ferro Metals Ltd (IFM) is an Australia-based ferrochrome producer. The Companys production facilities are located in the North West Province of South Africa. IFM produces ferrochrome from chromite ore located in the Bushveld Igneous Complex. IFMs Lesedi chromite mine and smelting operations are situated at Buffelsfontein, 100 kilometers north-west of Johannesburg, South Africa. The Company holds an 80% interest in its nearby Sky Chrome deposit. The Companys total installed capacity is approximately 265,000 tonnes of ferrochrome per annum. The Company operates in one business segment, being the mining and processing of chromite in South Africa and sale of ferrochrome. The Companys subsidiaries include International Ferro Metals (SA) (Pty) Ltd, Purity Metals Holdings Ltd, Sky Chrome Mining (Pty) Ltd and International Ferro Metals SA Holdings (Pty) Ltd.</Text>
		<Text Type="Financial Summary" lastModified="2015-02-25T09:15:24">BRIEF: For the six months ended 31 December 2014, International Ferro Metals Limited revenues increased 2% to RAN1.02B. Net loss totaled RAN174.8M vs. income of RAN32.7M. Revenues reflect an increase in demand for the Company's products and services due to favorable market conditions. Net loss reflects Finance costs increase of 15% to RAN37.3M (expense), Unabsorbed Fixed Costs increase of 8% to RAN20M (expense).</Text>
	</TextInfo>
